{{else}}
<p>Now that your Ubuntu is ready to use, we need to install some basic requirements before we can proceed:</p>
<p>1. Open terminal and run <code> sudo apt-get update</code> in order to update any leftover package.</p>
<p>2. Now run the following commands in order install Git, NPM, NodeJS and some other necessary packages:</p>
<ol>
  <li><code>sudo apt-get install git</code></li>
  <li><code>sudo apt-get install npm</code></li>
</ol>
<p>3. Now run <code>npm -v</code> and you should receive a version of NPM installed. If you do, then let's keep going:</p>
<ol>
  <li><code>sudo npm cache clean -f</code></li>
  <li><code>sudo npm install -g n</code></li>
  <li><code>sudo n stable</code></li>
  <li><code>sudo chown -R $(whoami) $(npm config get prefix)/{lib/node_modules,bin,share}</code></li>
</ol>
<p>4. Now run <code>node -v</code> and you should receive the latest stable Node installed. If you do, then let's keep going again:</p>
<ol>
  <li><code>npm install ember-cli -g</code></li>
  <li><code>npm install bower -g</code></li>
  <li><code>wget -O- https://toolbelt.heroku.com/install-ubuntu.sh | sh</code></li>
</ol>
<p>5. Run <code>ember -v</code> and you should get a number for response. If so, restart the machine as we are now going to the project dependencies:</p>
<p></p>
